## Rules

### FRONT-001: Component Size
severity: ERROR
scope: all UI components
rule: UI components MUST NOT exceed the configured line limit. Components that mix data fetching with rendering MUST be split into container and presentational components.
threshold: max_component_lines=150, max_props=10
example_correct: |
  // UserCard.tsx — pure presentational
  export const UserCard = ({ name, email }: UserCardProps) => (
    <div>{name} — {email}</div>
  );
example_incorrect: |
  // UserCard.tsx — 300 lines mixing fetch + render

### FRONT-002: Prop Drilling Limit
severity: WARNING
scope: component tree depth
rule: Props MUST NOT be drilled more than 3 levels deep without using a context or state management solution. Components receiving props they do not use MUST be refactored.
threshold: max_props=10, max_drill_depth=3
example_correct: |
  // Use context for deeply shared state
  const { user } = useUserContext();
example_incorrect: |
  <GrandChild user={user} />  // passed through 4 layers unused
